All of this applies a level of immersion that is unrivaled within the entertainment industry, some wonderfully gorgeous games have been created for VR or adapted to VR. Ever wanted to explore inside the world of Skyrim? Well you can with VR, exploring vast scenic landscapes and being a part of the world is something that has really boosted these systems into popularity.
Virtual reality has recently had some time under the spotlight but what is it? Virtual reality isn’t anything too new, however recently the technology behind it has improved enough for it to become a common thing. Although a bit on the pricy end if you are looking for high end gear you can also purchase a lower end product, consoles have a good value option but you can even experiment with it using a phone app and some cardboard.
What is needed to use this? Well for an honest and true VR set you would need a camera, gloves/ controls, and the headset itself. Although some have managed to go without a need of a camera. The basis of this is that the camera tracks your movement which then correlates with you within the game world. And the headset displays the screen in a way which makes them appear real instead of a TV in front of your face, while also controlling the view from the screen with your head movements.
